      • isCommittable

        public boolean isCommittable()
        Description copied from interface: ClickToEditForm.Field
        Check if the editor for this form field is committable. Some editor UI's may commit changes as soon as the user requests them, in which case the commit method won't be called and instead of showing save/cancel buttons to the user, a "close" button will be shown instead.
        Specified by:
        isCommittable in interface ClickToEditForm.Field
        Returns:
        true if the editor supports ClickToEditForm.Field.commit(Component, List) and therefore the container should show save/cancel buttons for the editor.
